Holotype: 1 male (IEBR-Myr 131H) Vietnam, Kon Tum Prov., Ngoc Linh Mts. (
107°58'30"E
; 
15°04'09"N
), primary forest, 1,900 m a.s.l., pitfall traps, 29 March - 4 April 2006, leg. Nguyen A.D.

Epiproct (ep) (Fig. 1D, 
E-F
) long, but broadly truncated, with four spinnerets at tip. Hypoproct (hp) roundly triangular, with two separated, distolateral, setiferous knobs.

Legs (Figs 1
A-E
) thin and slender, about 1.3 times as long as midbody height. Prefemora not swollen. Femora without modification. Tarsal brushes present only on pre-gonopodal legs.
